item.description:
【<p>To simulate real user behavior, performance tests often rely on API keys, tokens, or credentials to interact with real systems. But as your testing suite grows, this sensitive data can start to sprawl across scripts, configs, and environments, increasing the risk of exposure and making tests harder to manage and maintain. </p><p>To address this challenge, we’re rolling out <strong>secrets management for </strong><u><strong><a href="https://grafana.com/products/cloud/k6/?pg=performance-testing-best-practices-how-to-prepare-for-peak-demand-with-grafana-cloud-k6&plcmt=in-text">Grafana Cloud k6</a></strong></u>, the fully managed performance testing platform powered by k6 OSS. Secrets management allows you to securely store and use sensitive values in your load tests. This means if your tests rely on API tokens, credentials, or any other confidential data, you no longer need to hardcode them into your scripts or pass them around manually.</p><p>With secrets management, secrets are stored centrally in Grafana Cloud and injected into your tests at runtime. This keeps your scripts clean, avoids accidental leaks in version control, and makes it easier to reuse the same test across environments. </p><p>Here’s a look at how to get started. </p><h2>Getting started: How to manage secrets from the Grafana Cloud UI</h2><p>Secrets can be created and managed directly from the Grafana Cloud web UI. To access them, navigate to <strong>Testing & synthetics</strong> > <strong>Performance</strong> > <strong>Settings</strong>, and open the <strong>Secrets</strong> tab from the menu.</p><p>From this interface, you can perform all the basic lifecycle operations:</p><ul><li><strong>Create secrets</strong> by providing a name, description, and value. The name is how the secret will be referenced in your tests, and the value is the sensitive data itself. Once saved, the secret becomes immediately available to your tests. For each secret, you can also write a description (e.g., to explain the secret’s purpose) and use labels to help with organization.</li><li><strong>Edit secrets</strong> to modify their values, descriptions, or labels. Note that editing a secret does not reveal its current value; instead, you provide a new value that replaces the previous one. This ensures that secrets are never exposed through the UI after they are initially set. If you need to rotate credentials, you can simply overwrite the existing secret with a new value.</li><li><strong>Delete secrets</strong> that are no longer needed.</li></ul><p>A key design principle here is that <strong>secret values are write-only in the UI</strong>. After creation, they cannot be read back or displayed. This prevents accidental exposure through screenshots, screen sharing, or casual inspection, and aligns with common security practices.</p><h2>Using secrets in your Grafana Cloud k6 tests</h2><p>Once your secrets are defined, using them in your tests is simple. Grafana Cloud k6 provides a dedicated module, <code>k6/secrets</code>, which allows you to retrieve secret values at runtime.</p><p>You can import the module and access a secret by its name:</p><p></p><pre><code>import check from "k6";
import http from 'k6/http';
import secrets from 'k6/secrets';
export default async function main () {
const apiToken = await secrets.get('api-token');
const headers = {
Authorization: `Bearer ${apiToken}`,
};
console.log("Headers: " + JSON.stringify(headers))
let res = http.get('https://example.com/api', {headers: headers});
check(res, { "get executions status is 200": (res) => res.status === 200 });
}
</code></pre><p>In this example, the secret "api-token" is fetched when the test runs and used as part of an HTTP request. From the script's perspective, the returned value behaves like a regular string, so you can use it anywhere you would normally use a variable.</p><p>This makes it easy to integrate secrets into existing scripts without major refactoring. You can gradually replace hardcoded values or environment variables with secrets managed in Grafana Cloud.</p><p>Secrets are also protected during test execution. If a secret is accidentally logged, its value will not be exposed in the logs. Instead, it will be redacted automatically. This reduces the risk of leaking sensitive data through debugging output or test results. Combined with write-only storage in the UI, this ensures that secrets remain protected throughout their lifecycle: from creation, to usage in tests, to observability outputs.</p><h2>Learn more </h2><p>Secrets management in Grafana Cloud k6 is available now in public preview. The feature is also <u><a href="https://grafana.com/blog/how-to-create-and-manage-secrets-with-grafana-cloud-synthetic-monitoring">generally available in Grafana Cloud Synthetic Monitoring</a></u>, a black box monitoring solution powered by k6 that lets you proactively assess system reliability and performance.</p><p>To learn more, please visit our <u><a href="https://grafana.com/docs/grafana-cloud/testing/k6/author-run/manage-secrets/">documentation</a></u>. </p><p><u><em><a href="https://grafana.com/products/cloud/?pg=blog&plcmt=body-txt">Grafana Cloud</a></em></u><em> is the easiest way to get started with k6 and performance testing. We have a generous forever-free tier and plans for every use case. </em><u><em><a href="https://grafana.com/auth/sign-up/create-user/?src=k6io&redirectPath=k6&pg=blog&plcmt=body-txt">Sign up for free now!</a></em></u> </p>】<p>为了模拟真实的用户行为，性能测试通常依赖 API 密钥、令牌或凭据与真实系统进行交互。但随着测试套件的增长，这些敏感数据可能开始跨脚本、配置和环境蔓延，从而增加暴露的风险，并使测试更难以管理和维护。 </p><p>为了应对这一挑战，我们正在推出<strong>秘密管理</strong><u><strong><a href="https://grafana.com/products/cloud/k6/?pg=performance-testing-best-practices-how-to-prepare-for-peak-demand-with-grafana-cloud-k6&plcmt=in-text">Grafana Cloud k6</a></strong></u>，由 k6 OSS 提供支持的完全托管的性能测试平台。机密管理允许您在负载测试中安全地存储和使用敏感值。这意味着，如果您的测试依赖于 API 令牌、凭据或任何其他机密数据，您不再需要将它们硬编码到脚本中或手动传递它们。</p><p>通过机密管理，机密将集中存储在 Grafana Cloud 中，并在运行时注入到您的测试中。这可以保持脚本干净，避免版本控制中的意外泄漏，并且可以更轻松地跨环境重用相同的测试。 </p><p>以下是如何开始。 </p><h2>入门：如何从 Grafana Cloud UI 管理机密</h2><p>可以直接从 Grafana Cloud Web UI 创建和管理机密。要访问它们，请导航至<strong>测试和合成</strong> > <strong>性能</strong> > <strong>设置</strong>，然后从菜单中打开<strong>机密</strong>选项卡。</p><p>在此界面中，您可以执行所有基本生命周期操作：</p><ul><li><strong>通过提供名称、描述和值创建机密</strong>。名称是在测试中引用机密的方式，值是敏感数据本身。保存后，该秘密将立即可供您的测试使用。对于每个秘密，您还可以编写描述（例如，解释秘密的用途）并使用标签来帮助组织。</li><li><strong>编辑秘密</strong>以修改其值、描述或标签。请注意，编辑机密不会泄露其当前值；相反，您提供一个新值来替换前一个值。这可确保秘密在最初设置后永远不会通过 UI 暴露。如果您需要轮换凭据，只需用新值覆盖现有密钥即可。</li><li><strong>删除不再需要的密钥</strong>。</li></ul><p>这里的一个关键设计原则是<strong>密钥值在 UI 中是只写的</strong>。创建后，它们无法读回或显示。这可以防止通过屏幕截图、屏幕共享或临时检查意外泄露，并符合常见的安全实践。</p><h2>在 Grafana Cloud k6 测试中使用机密</h2><p>定义机密后，在测试中使用它们就很简单。 Grafana Cloud k6 提供了专用的模块 <code>k6/secrets</code>，它允许您在运行时检索机密值。</p><p>您可以导入模块并通过其名称访问机密：</p><p></p><pre><code>import check from "k6";
从'k6/http'导入http；
从“k6/secrets”导入机密；
导出默认异步函数 main () {
const apiToken =等待secrets.get('api-token');
常量标头 = {
授权：`不记名${apiToken}`，
};
console.log("标题：" + JSON.stringify(标题))
让 res = http.get('https://example.com/api', {headers: headers});
check(res, { "获取执行状态为 200": (res) => res.status === 200 });
}
</code></pre><p>在此示例中，测试运行时会获取秘密“api-token”并将其用作 HTTP 请求的一部分。从脚本的角度来看，返回值的行为类似于常规字符串，因此您可以在通常使用变量的任何地方使用它。</p><p>这使得可以轻松地将机密集成到现有脚本中，而无需进行重大重构。您可以逐步使用 Grafana Cloud 中管理的机密替换硬编码值或环境变量。</p><p>机密在测试执行期间也会受到保护。如果意外记录了机密，则其值不会在日志中公开。相反，它将被自动编辑。这降低了通过调试输出或测试结果泄露敏感数据的风险。与 UI 中的只写存储相结合，这可确保机密在其整个生命周期中始终受到保护：从创建到测试中的使用，再到可观察性输出。</p><h2>了解更多信息</h2><p>Grafana Cloud k6 中的机密管理现已推出公共预览版。该功能还<u><a href="https://grafana.com/blog/how-to-create-and-manage-secrets-with-grafana-cloud-synthetic-monitoring">在 Grafana Cloud Synthetic Monitoring 中普遍可用</a></u>，这是一种由 k6 提供支持的黑盒监控解决方案，可让您主动评估系统可靠性和性能。</p><p>要了解更多信息，请访问我们的<u><a href="https://grafana.com/docs/grafana-cloud/testing/k6/author-run/manage-secrets/">文档</a></u>。 </p><p><u><em><a href="https://grafana.com/products/cloud/?pg=blog&plcmt=body-txt">Grafana Cloud</a></em></u><em>是开始进行 k6 和性能测试的最简单方法。我们为每个用例提供慷慨的永久免费套餐和计划。 </em><u><em><a href="https://grafana.com/auth/sign-up/create-user/?src=k6io&redirectPath=k6&pg=blog&plcmt=body-txt">立即免费注册！</a></em></u> </p>
